balanceOf(address).details: Returns the number of NFTs owned by `_owner`.      Throws if `_owner` is the zero address. NFTs assigned to the zero address are considered invalid.

params._owner: Address for whom to query the balance.

constructor.details: Proxy pattern contract - disable initializers for implementation on deployment

params._lock_duration: Number of seconds to lock tokens for (rounded down to nearest week)
Number of seconds to lock tokens for (rounded down to nearest week)

params.delegatee: The address to cast your total voting power.

deposit_for(uint256,uint256).details: Anyone (even a smart contract) can deposit for someone else, but      cannot extend their locktime and deposit for a brand new user

params._value: Amount to add to user's lock

getApproved(uint256).details: Get the approved address for a single NFT.

params._tokenId: ID of the NFT to query the approval of.

getPastTotalSupply(uint256).details: The name `getPastTotalSupply` is maintained to keep in-line with IVotes interface, but it actually returns      total vote power. For current total supply of NFTs, call `totalSupply`.

getPastVotes(address,uint256).details: The votes are calculated at the upper checkpoint of a binary search on that user's delegation history.

params.account: The address to get votes for.
params.timepoint: The timestamp to get votes for.

params._value: Amount of tokens to deposit and add to the lock

params._lock_duration: New number of seconds until tokens unlock

params.base_uri: Base URI for token ID images

isApprovedForAll(address,address).details: Checks if `_operator` is an approved operator for `_owner`.

params._operator: The address that acts on behalf of the owner.
params._owner: The address that owns the NFTs.

liquidate(uint256).details: User is penalized 50% of their remaining voting power in underlying tokens, transferred to the DAO treasury. e.g. Unlock at 4 years before end => user is penalized 50% of tokens      Unlock at 3 years before end => user is penalized 37.5% of tokens      Unlock at 2 years before end => user is penalized 25% of tokens      Unlock at 1 year before end => user is penalized 12.5% of tokens      Unlock on/after end => user is not penalized.Minimum value to withdraw is 100 gwei, to prevent liquidation of low voting power, as this can      potentially lead to zero penalty.

returns._0: Epoch time of the lock end

merge(uint256,uint256).details: End timestamp of merge is value-weighted based on composite tokens.

params._from: The token ID that gets burned.
params._to: The token ID that burned token gets merged into.

ownerOf(uint256).details: Returns the address of the owner of the NFT.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Transfers the ownership of an NFT from one address to another address.      Throws unless `msg.sender` is the current owner, an authorized operator, or the      approved address for this NFT.      Throws if `_from` is not the current owner.      Throws if `_to` is the zero address.      Throws if `_tokenId` is not a valid NFT.      If `_to` is a smart contract, it calls `onERC721Received` on `_to` and throws if      the return value is not `bytes4(keccak256("onERC721Received(address,address,uint,bytes)"))`.

params._from: The current owner of the NFT.

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: Enables or disables approval for a third party ("operator") to manage all of      `msg.sender`'s assets. It also emits the ApprovalForAll event.      Throws if `_operator` is the `msg.sender`. (NOTE: This is not written the EIP)

params._approved: True if the operators is approved, false to revoke approval.
params._operator: Address to add to the set of authorized operators.

params._extraction: The underlying value to be used to make a new NFT.
params._tokenId: The token ID to be split.
Token ID to fetch URI for.

params._block: Block to calculate the total voting power at

totalPowerAtT(uint256).details: Adheres to the ERC20 `totalSupply` interface for Aragon compatibility

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Throws unless `msg.sender` is the current owner, an authorized operator, or the approved address for this NFT.      Throws if `_from` is not the current owner.      Throws if `_to` is the zero address.      Throws if `_tokenId` is not a valid NFT.

params._from: The current owner of the NFT.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

withdraw(uint256).details: Only possible if the lock has expired

enableLiquidations().notice: One time use flag to enable liquidations.

getPastTotalSupply(uint256).notice: The total voting power at a historic timestamp.

getPastVotes(address,uint256).notice: Governor compliant method for counting voting power of an address at a historic timestamp, by getting         their balance of token IDs at that timestamp and the corresponding vote power of each one at that time.

getVotes(address).notice: Governor compliant method for counting current voting power of an address.

get_last_user_slope(uint256).notice: Get the most recently recorded rate of voting power decrease for `_tokenId`

increase_amount(uint256,uint256).notice: Deposit `_value` additional tokens for `_tokenId` without modifying the unlock time

liquidate(uint256).notice: Opt-out mechanism for users to liquidate their veCTM anytime before end timestamp, incurring a penalty.

merge(uint256,uint256).notice: Merge two token IDs and combine their underlying values.

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).notice: This works even if sender doesn't own any tokens at the time.

setTreasury(address).notice: Set the address of the receiver of liquidation penalties.

setUp(address,address,address,address).notice: Because Voting Escrow is deployed before other contracts, we need a setup function.

split(uint256,uint256).notice: Split into two NFTs, with a new one created with an extracted value.

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: ERC165 compliant method for checking supported interfaces.

tokenIdsDelegatedTo(address).notice: Get the list of token IDs that are currently delegated to `account`.

tokenIdsDelegatedToAt(address,uint256).notice: Get the list of token IDs that were delegated to `account` at historic timestamp.
